conbody.p: Create a dimension that measure the length of an arc or polyarc. The dimension is based on the current dimension style. Options allow you to include a leader and specify the angle and contents of the dimension text.

section.title: Methods to create an arc length dimension
section.p: There is one method to begin creating an arc length dimension:

ul.li: Select arc or polyline arc segment

dlentry.dt: Select arc or polyline arc segment
dlentry.dd: Begin creating an arc length dimension by selecting an arc or polyline arc segment then:
Specify a point to locate the position of the dimension arc.

section.title: Options within the DIMARC command
section.p: After you begin creating an arc length dimension, the following options may be available:

dlentry.dd: Specify the angle of the dimension text. A value of 0 aligns the dimension text with the dimension line. Any other value rotates the dimension text relative to the x-axis of the current UCS.

Enter text to override the default dimension text which includes the measured length of the dimension. You can use two angle brackets <> to display the measured length of the dimension in addition to other text.
Specify a point for the first extension line then:

dlentry.dt: Specify second point for arc length dimension
dlentry.dd: Specify a point for the second extension line.
Specify the location of the dimension line.
Toggle on a leader from the dimension text to the arc.

dd.p: Toggle off the leader from the dimension text to the arc.
